==English==

===Pronunciation===
*stēp, /stiːp/, /<tt>sti:p</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːp|Rhymes: -iːp]]

===Etymology 1===
{{OE.}} ''steap'', a cliff

===Adjective===
'''steep'''

#Of a near-vertical [[gradient]]
#''(Informal)'' [[Expensive]]
#:''That's a bit '''steep'''. ''

====Translations====
*French: [[escarpé]]

===Etymology 2===

{{OE.}} ''stepan'', a drinking vessel

===Noun===
'''steep'''
#A [[liquid]] used in a steeping process

===Verb===
{{regverb|'''steep'''|'''[[steep]]'''|'''[[steeped]]'''|'''[[steeping]]'''}}
'''steep'''
#To soak an item (or to be soaked) in liquid in order to gradually add or remove ingredients from the item
#: '''Skins are steeped in a tanning solution to create leather'''
#To be [[imbued]] with an [[abstract]] [[quality]]
#: '''A town steeped in history'''
#{{US}} To make tea (or other beverage) by placing leaves in hot water.



